<h1>CHAPTER 4: SYSTEM IMPLEMENTATION AND TESTING</h1>

<h2>4.1 Technologies and Tools Used</h2>
<p>The KaviCakes Management System employs a decentralized micro-frontend architecture paired with a centralized backend. Operational files (e.g., payment deposit slips) are stored on local server directories, while static legacy assets utilize Supabase cloud storage. A MySQL relational database guarantees data persistence, enforcing referential integrity between orders, loyalty caps, and dynamic pricing metrics.</p>

<h2>4.2 User Interfaces and Interaction Flow</h2>
<p>The client-side experience is explicitly segregated into two distinct portals: the <strong>Customer Web Portal</strong> and the <strong>Admin Control Center</strong>. Use of strict role-based access control (RBAC) ensures data integrity and security across all transactional endpoints.</p>

<h3>4.3.1 Customer Web Capability & Interfaces</h3>

<h4>4.3.1.1 Authentication & User Acquisition</h4>
<p>The system utilizes a secure join-flow requiring email verification. The login and registration interfaces are built using Tailwind CSS for high responsiveness and include real-time verification status indicators.</p>

<div class="figure-container">
    <img src="../system's screenshots/customer/create an account.png" alt="Registration Page">
    <span class="caption">Figure 4.1: Secure Customer Registration Interface with Phone & Address Mapping</span>
</div>

<div class="figure-container">
    <img src="../system's screenshots/customer/login.png" alt="Login Page">
    <span class="caption">Figure 4.2: Role-based Authentication Portal</span>
</div>

