<h3>4.3.4 Roles & Interaction Protocols</h3>
<p>Data synchronization between roles occurs via a structured API pipe. When a customer performs a transactional action (e.g., slip upload), the corresponding administrative workstation is updated in real-time, enforcing a logical preparation-block until verification clears.</p>

<h3>4.3.5 Strict Order Progression Model</h3>
<table>
    <tr>
        <th>State</th>
        <th>Visual Outcome</th>
        <th>System Validation Rules</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>NEW</strong></td>
        <td>Admin Confirmation Queue</td>
        <td>Validates Loyalty integer capping <= 30%. Calculates sub-48-hour delivery dates forcibly imposing priority fees.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>CONFIRMED</strong></td>
        <td>Payment Verification List</td>
        <td>Automatically invokes SMTP functions executing direct confirmation alerts securely to customer mail.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>PREPARING</strong></td>
        <td>Production Floor Cards</td>
        <td><strong>Hard Block:</strong> Restricts status mutation. API explicitly rejects the change unless Payment_Verified = True.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>READY</strong></td>
        <td>Delivery Schedule Dispatch</td>
        <td>Automatically triggers frontend dashboard notification variables targeting specific tracking UI components.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>DELIVERED</strong></td>
        <td>Archived Order History</td>
        <td>Resolves order fields generating backend PDF scripts pushing exact billing parameters asynchronously.</td>
    </tr>
</table>

